<div class="alert alert-secondary mb-3" role="alert">
  This example shows you a full cycle. You can ask for an amount and enter a test credit card number like 4111 1111 1111
  1111 and observe how the backend processes this payment for you and returns events data via (webhook or polling). For
  our example we will rely on polling since this is most likely running on developer desktop behind a firewall. For
  production you would more likely rely on webhook post. You will need to configure <a href="/poller">Poll Events</a>
  before you can see a response return.For mobile apps consider also supplying external device ID, the response will
  return it and allow you to send push notifications if needed.
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-3">
    <form action="#" class="mt-3" id="payment_form">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="payment_reference">Details for payment (optional)</label>
        <input type="text" value="" class="form-control" id="payment_reference" name="payment_reference">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="payment_amount">Total amount (required)</label>
        <input type="number"
               value="10"
               step="0.01"
               min="0.5"
               required
               oninvalid="this.setCustomValidity('This field is required')"
               oninput="this.setCustomValidity('')"
               class="form-control"
               id="payment_amount"
               name="payment_amount">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="external_device_id">External device ID (optional)</label>
        <input type="text" value="" class="form-control" id="external_device_id" name="external_device_id">
      </div>
      <button class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-block" id="request_payment">Request</button>
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <iframe id="payment_cycle"></iframe>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-3">
    <div class="table-responsive">
      <table id="xcoobee_api_result" class="table table-responsive table-hover">
        <thead>
        <tr>
          <th width="20%">Event</th>
          <th width="40%">Payload</th>
          <th width="20%">Reference</th>
          <th width="200px">Date Created</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="xcoobee_loader">
      <img alt="" src="/images/loader.svg" />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

